                        "content": "The student nurse is preparing a presentation on circumstances in the health care environment that increase moral injury during the COVID-19 pandemic. Which scenario in the presentation would prompt the need for further teaching by the nurse educator?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "c2472dbaf30269ec1d4a4af474a31869",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Understanding 理解",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nMoral injury is the damage done to one’s conscience or moral compass when that person perpetrates, witnesses, or fails to prevent acts that transgress one’s own moral beliefs, values, or ethical codes of conduct. Having a fully staffed unit would not be a situation that would cause moral injury because ample support would be provided to the staff so that they could provide care to clients.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions\nCognitive Ability: Understanding\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Moral Injury\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Stress and Coping, Caregiving\nStrategies: Negative Event Query, Strategic Words, Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, circumstances that increase moral injury. Note the strategic words, need for further teaching. These words indicate a negative event query and ask you to select an option that is an incorrect statement. Think about the description of moral injury to assist in answering correctly.\n ",
